Travel Itinerary 
Create a program to organize a travel itinerary. The program will store information about different destinations, including the city name, country, duration of stay, and budget. It will prompt the user to enter details for three destinations, validate the data types, and display this information in a structured format.

Requirements:

Variables: Use variables to store information about each destination.

Casting: Ensure that the duration of stay and budget are stored as integers.
Data Types: Use appropriate data types for different pieces of information.

Lists: Store the details of the destinations in a list.

Dictionaries: Use dictionaries to store information about each destination.

Sample Input:
Enter the name of the first city: Paris 
Enter the name of the country for the first city: France
Enter the duration of stay (in days) for the first city: 5
Enter the budget (in dollars) for the first city: 1000

Enter the name of the second city: Tokyo
Enter the name of the country for the second city: Japan
Enter the duration of stay (in days) for the second city: 7
Enter the budget (in dollars) for the second city: 1500

Enter the name of the third city: New York 
Enter the name of the country for the third city: USA 
Enter the duration of stay (in days) for the third city: 3 
Enter the budget (in dollars) for the third city: 800

Sample Out:
Travel Itinerary:

City: Paris
Country: France
Duration of Stay: 5 days
Budget: $1000

City: Tokyo
Country: Japan
Duration of Stay: 7days
Budget: $1500

City: New York
Country: USA
Duration of Stay: 3 days
Budget: $800
